Commentary Text: Sangwan to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Shubman Gill!! Patidar falls in a bid to up the ante! With square leg and fine leg up, he was looking to counter the wide line with a big shuffle across and scoop. Sangwan though, does well to follow the batter and although it's a full toss, Patidar isn't in the best of position to make a clean connection. Ends up miscuing it straight to Gill at square leg. The shot was definitely on, just the execution didn't go to plan. A fantastic knock from the young man though. He's set it up well for the likes of Maxwell and DK to maximise the end overs.
